		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This basic research will establish a new notion of domain for use in the denotational semantics of programming languages. The new notion of domain has a simple definition using elementary concepts from topology. We shall demonstrate the ability of such  topological domains  to model an unprecedented variety of computational features in combination, thus resolving known problems arising in conventional domain theory.Applications of denotational semantics are, in general, facilitated through the provision of  computational metalanguages : theoretically tractable idealized programming languages into which other more realistic languages can be translated. We shall exploit the flexibility of topological domains by using them to model powerful computational metalanguages exhibiting interesting and novel syntactic and operational features.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
